Question: I'm joining the ECB on an indefinite contract next month. How long
  will my probationary period be and under what circumstances can it
  be extended?
Example answer: Appointments shall be subject to a probationary period of six months
  unless the Chief Services Officer, on behalf of the Executive Board,
  decides to waive it. Where the probationer is prevented by illness,
  accident, maternity or, in exceptional circumstances, special leave
  from performing their duties for a period of more than one month,
  the probationary period may be extended accordingly; in addition, in
  exceptional circumstances the Chief Services Officer may extend the
  probationary period up to a maximum of twelve months, with or
  without assigning the probationer to another function. The
  probationary period shall in no circumstances exceed twelve months,
  and a member of staff shall not be subject to more than one
  probationary period for the same or an equivalent position. (ECB
  Conditions of Employment, page 6; ECB Staff Rules, pages 47–48)
